    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 5: \"The adaptor protein Fe65 (APBB1) is present in Schaffer collaterals/CA1 dendritic spine hippocampal synapses where it colocalizes with P2X2 subunits.\n...\nH-K, electron micrographs showing double immunogold labeling for P2X2 subunits (5 nm) and Fe65 (10 nm). Only the postsynaptic specialization of CA1 synapses presented labeling for both proteins\"\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Light and Electron Microscopy\nFour postnatal day 35 Sprague-Dawley rats were transcardially perfused. \"\n\nantibody:\n\"The analysis of the localization of Fe65 and P2X2 receptor subunits was performed as described (23.)\" PMID:11160443",
